divs: Sighting DetailsI was on my balcony having a cigerette with my daughter oct 3rd at 7pm when I first and then my adult daughter saw The object that glowed a bright orange-similar to a fire and looked as if it was a rocket-(large) headed north-west.I first thought it was a large airplane similar to the space shuttle on fire and watched the object with my adult daughter ascend toward the moon-twilight-7pm for 1 or 2 minutes and then descend rapidly until it disappeared over the horizen 2 minutes later.Ive seen airplanes and they don't fly in an arc.We both kinda laughed it off by saying that was weird...couldn't be a UFO right?...hmm we checked the news and didn't see anything about it. My impression is that it may have been a weapons test from a military installation, a satellite launch, a Meteor, or some space junk falling from the sky or maybe something unexplainable.I know it was brightly visable to thousands of people so my daughter and I can't be the only people to observe this object.Maybe somebody else saw this from a different angle and got a better observation.
